# Cucumber Feature File Writer Skill (Gherkin BDD)

## What is a Feature File?
A `.feature` file is a plain English description of what your application should do,
written in a format called **Gherkin**. It acts as both documentation AND test cases.

---

## Gherkin Keywords

| Keyword | Purpose | Example |
|---------|---------|---------|
| `Feature` | Name of the feature being tested | `Feature: User Login` |
| `Background` | Steps that run before EVERY scenario | `Background: Given user is on homepage` |
| `Scenario` | A single test case | `Scenario: Successful login` |
| `Scenario Outline` | Parameterized test (runs multiple times) | `Scenario Outline: Login with <role>` |
| `Examples` | Data table for Scenario Outline | `Examples: \| user \| admin \|` |
| `Given` | Precondition / setup state | `Given the user is on the login page` |
| `When` | The action the user performs | `When the user clicks the login button` |
| `Then` | The expected result | `Then the user should see the dashboard` |
| `And` | Continue previous Given/When/Then | `And the user enters valid password` |
| `But` | Negative continuation | `But the error message should not appear` |
| `@tag` | Group/filter scenarios | `@smoke @regression` |

---

## Feature File Template

```gherkin
@login @smoke
Feature: User Login
  As a registered user
  I want to log into the application
  So that I can access my account

  Background:
    Given the application is running
    And the user is on the login page

  @positive
  Scenario: Successful login with valid credentials
    When the user enters username "pavan@test.com" and password "Password@123"
    And the user clicks the login button
    Then the user should be redirected to the dashboard
    And the welcome message "Welcome, Pavan!" should be displayed

  @negative
  Scenario: Login fails with invalid password
    When the user enters username "pavan@test.com" and password "WrongPass"
    And the user clicks the login button
    Then an error message "Invalid credentials" should be displayed
    And the user should remain on the login page

  @smoke
  Scenario Outline: Login with different user roles
    When the user enters username "<username>" and password "<password>"
    And the user clicks the login button
    Then the user should see the "<dashboard>" dashboard

    Examples:
      | username         | password      | dashboard |
      | admin@test.com   | Admin@123     | Admin     |
      | viewer@test.com  | Viewer@123    | Viewer    |
      | editor@test.com  | Editor@123    | Editor    |
```

