## Gherkin Best Practices

### ✅ DO
- Write steps from the **user's perspective** ("the user clicks..." not "click button")
- Keep scenarios **independent** — each should work on its own
- Use **Background** for repeated Given steps across all scenarios
- Use **Scenario Outline + Examples** for data-driven tests (same flow, different data)
- Add **tags** (`@smoke`, `@regression`, `@login`) to group tests
- Keep scenarios **short** — ideally 3–7 steps
- Write in **present tense** ("the user is", "the page shows")

### ❌ DON'T
- Don't mention UI details like button colors or CSS classes
  - ❌ `When the user clicks the blue submit button at the bottom right`
  - ✅ `When the user clicks the login button`
- Don't write implementation details
  - ❌ `When the POST request is sent to /api/login`
  - ✅ `When the user submits the login form`
- Don't create dependent scenarios (Scenario 2 relying on Scenario 1 passing)
- Don't write more than 10 steps in one scenario — split into smaller ones

