## Tags Strategy

| Tag | When to Use |
|-----|-------------|
| `@smoke` | Critical happy path tests — run on every build |
| `@regression` | Full suite — run before releases |
| `@positive` | Tests expected to succeed |
| `@negative` | Tests for error/failure cases |
| `@wip` | Work in progress — exclude from CI |
| `@<feature-name>` | Group by feature: `@login`, `@checkout` |

---

## File Naming & Location
- Location: `src/test/resources/features/`
- File name: lowercase with hyphens → `user-login.feature`, `product-search.feature`
- One feature per file (don't mix login and checkout in same file)

---

## Output Format When Writing Feature Files
1. Show complete `.feature` file
2. List the step definition method signatures that will be needed
3. Note which steps can be reused from existing step definitions
4. Suggest tags based on the scenario type
